{# ── Welcome ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #}
<section class="section--sm">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="prose reveal">
      <h2>Welcome</h2>
      <p>Many people who seek God find themselves navigating theological frameworks that, however well-intentioned, can create deep spiritual fragmentation. The language of faith, meant to be a source of life, can sometimes become a source of shame, pressure, and constant performance anxiety.</p>
      <p>The Kerygma Codex was created as a response to this pain. It is not a new doctrine, a rulebook, or a diagnostic system — it is a shared language for repair, offered as a commons of healing for those longing for a faith that is both trustworthy and safe. It imagines faith less like a performance system and more like a <em>garden of chapels</em>: a place of rest, consent, and careful discernment.</p>
      <p>You do not need to read everything to begin. Return slowly. This is not a system to complete — it is a garden to walk in.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

